items.title: Eurostar disruption to continue after power outage in Channel Tunnel
items.description: Eurostar services will resume with severe delays and possible cancellations after services were suspended due to a power supply problem.

items.title: Guinea junta chief takes lead in controversial election as social media restricted
items.description: TikTok, YouTube and Facebook are down, as the nation awaits the final result from the presidential poll.

items.title: K-pop band member sued for $30m after bitter record label feud
items.description: Record label Ador says it has dropped NewJeans member Danielle Marsh while the return of Minji remains uncertain.

items.title: Saudi Arabia backs call for UAE to leave Yemen after strike on separatist-held port
items.description: The UAE denies Saudi claims it sent a shipment of weapons to separatists and pushed them to launch offensives against the Yemeni government.

items.title: Ukraine denies drone attack on Putin's residence
items.description: Russia has accused Ukraine of targeting a presidential residence, which President Zelensky called "typical Russian lies".
